---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Icon from '../../../components/Icon.astro';
import Card from '../../../components/Card.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Week 9: The P4 Cut-Up — Figma → Semantic HTML5 - DESN 368">
    <nav class="breadcrumb-nav">
        <div class="breadcrumb-container">
            <div class="breadcrumb">
                <a href="/1">Course Overview</a>
                <span class="breadcrumb-separator">></span>
                <span class="breadcrumb-current">Week 9: The P4 Cut-Up</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <main class="course-content two-column">
        <div class="main-content fade-in">
            <Card variant="accent" class="card-enhanced">
                <div class="color-bar color-bar-red"></div>
                <SectionHeader level={1} icon="layers" badge={{ text: "This Week", variant: "info" }}>
                    Week 9: The P4 Cut-Up &mdash; Figma &rarr; Semantic HTML5
                </SectionHeader>
                <p class="subtitle">Spring 2026 &middot; Week 9</p>
                <p>You designed it in Figma. Now you cut it into semantic HTML5 using Antigravity &mdash; an AI IDE that maps your Figma layers into <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> tags with the required IDs and classes baked in.</p>
                <p>The catch: AI can't read what isn't there. <strong>Finishing your Figma IS doing your code.</strong> The cleaner your design, the faster the cut.</p>
            </Card>

            <div class="section-divider"></div>

            <Card variant="enhanced" class="card-enhanced">
                <SectionHeader icon="book" badge={{ text: "Tutorial", variant: "success" }}>
                    Tutorial &amp; Workflow
                </SectionHeader>

                <div class="resource-list">
                    <a href="/tutorials/p4-cutup-figma/" class="resource-item" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
                        <div class="resource-icon">
                            <Icon name="zap" size={20} />
                        </div>
                        <div class="resource-body">
                            <div class="resource-title">The P4 Cut-Up &mdash; Figma to Semantic HTML5</div>
                            <div class="resource-desc">Four-step workflow: Prime the agent &rarr; Constraint Cut &rarr; Logic Implementation (table + form) &rarr; Motion Audit. Includes a ~10-minute opencode + Figma MCP setup, the exact prompts to paste, and a "what the AI gets wrong" checklist.</div>
                        </div>
                        <Icon name="link" size={16} class="resource-arrow" />
                    </a>
                </div>
            </Card>

            <Card variant="enhanced" class="card-enhanced">
                <SectionHeader icon="check-circle" badge={{ text: "Due Before Next Class", variant: "warning" }}>
                    Checkpoint &mdash; P4 Cut-Up Submission
                </SectionHeader>
                <p>Once your Figma is finished and you've run the cut-up, submit two things to the Canvas assignment <strong>"P4 Cut-Up &mdash; First-Pass HTML + Prompt Log"</strong>:</p>
                <ol class="checkpoint-list">
                    <li>Your generated <code>index.html</code> &mdash; the semantic scaffold (CSS not graded yet).</li>
                    <li>A short prompt log: the 3-4 prompts you ran, plus one specific thing the AI got wrong and how you fixed it.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>Grading focuses on structural correctness (required IDs, classes, semantic tags all present) and evidence you read the AI's output critically. The full styled landing page is still due via the existing P4 Code submission.</p>
            </Card>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar">
            <section class="card card-action card-enhanced">
                <div class="color-bar color-bar-red"></div>
                <h3>
                    <span class="icon-enhanced icon-primary">
                        <Icon name="zap" size={20} />
                    </span>
                    Quick Actions
                </h3>
                <div class="quick-action-stack">
                    <a href="/1" class="btn btn-secondary">
                        <Icon name="book" size={16} class="btn-icon" />
                        Course Overview
                    </a>
                    <a href="/tutorials/p4-cutup-figma/" class="btn btn-start" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
                        <Icon name="play" size={16} class="btn-icon" />
                        Open the Cut-Up Tutorial
                    </a>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="card card-enhanced sidebar-note">
                <h3>
                    <span class="icon-enhanced icon-primary">
                        <Icon name="alert-circle" size={20} />
                    </span>
                    Figma Readiness
                </h3>
                <p>Before you start the cut-up, check your Figma:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Layers named like <code>Hero</code>, <code>Feature Card</code> &mdash; not <code>Frame 47</code>.</li>
                    <li>Sections grouped (hero, video, features, data, contact).</li>
                    <li>Motion annotations written as text labels next to elements.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>If your Figma fails this check, the cut-up will be slow and messy. Fix the Figma first.</p>
            </section>
        </aside>
    </main>

    <style>
        .subtitle {
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            margin-top: -8px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        .resource-list {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 12px;
        }

        .resource-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 14px;
            padding: 16px;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
            border-radius: 8px;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: inherit;
            background: var(--surface-alt);
            transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
        }

        .resource-item:hover {
            border-color: var(--brand-primary);
            background: var(--surface);
        }

        .resource-icon {
            flex-shrink: 0;
            width: 36px;
            height: 36px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            background: var(--eagle-red-light);
            border-radius: 8px;
            color: var(--eagle-red-text);
        }

        .resource-body {
            flex: 1;
            min-width: 0;
        }

        .resource-title {
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: var(--text-primary);
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }

        .resource-desc {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        .resource-arrow {
            flex-shrink: 0;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            margin-top: 2px;
        }

        .quick-action-stack {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 0.5rem;
        }

        .checkpoint-list {
            margin: 12px 0;
            padding-left: 22px;
        }

        .checkpoint-list li {
            margin: 6px 0;
        }

        .sidebar-note {
            margin-top: 16px;
        }

        .sidebar-note ul {
            padding-left: 18px;
            margin: 8px 0;
        }

        .sidebar-note li {
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            margin: 6px 0;
        }
    </style>
</BaseLayout>
